    "83cea298-5c41-4e10-8570-793e2a029c8d": {
      "type": "loop-article-richtext",
      "blocks": {
        "983426cb-d1e5-4a8e-8e2a-a660805e0286": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "3. Don’t Forget To Protect Your Ears",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "template--15787414028484__83cea298-5c41-4e10-8570-793e2a029c8d-1669993747b192658e-0": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Many people forget about ears when it comes to protection. But when wind gets inside your helmet it could cause long-term damage to your ears, even at lower speeds.<br\/><br\/>Surprised? Most people are.<br\/><br\/>Hearing damage can happen at any time over 85 dB and if you’re traveling at 100km\/h the db level is already around 94.<br\/><br\/>So one ride could cause you serious hearing issues.<br\/><br\/>You can protect your ears with <a href=\"https:\/\/www.loopearplugs.com\/pages\/earplugs-for-motorcycle\" title=\"https:\/\/www.loopearplugs.com\/pages\/earplugs-for-motorcycle\">earplugs that are specially designed<\/a> to reduce wind noise, but keep road noise clear. This way you can stay hyper-focused and alert with a sound reduction of up to 23 dB.<br\/><br\/>Your ears will thank you, promise.<\/p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "983426cb-d1e5-4a8e-8e2a-a660805e0286",
        "template--15787414028484__83cea298-5c41-4e10-8570-793e2a029c8d-1669993747b192658e-0"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "desktop_content_position": "left",
        "content_alignment": "left",
