    "c49dabfc-f0bd-4632-a097-f3ec01ded10c": {
      "type": "loop-article-richtext",
      "blocks": {
        "bd350321-2094-4451-ae70-e762f545bdb4": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "5.Check Your Bike",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "template--15787414028484__c49dabfc-f0bd-4632-a097-f3ec01ded10c-166999440929263ebf-0": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>We all lead busy lives. And of course, it can be tempting to skip getting your bike checked over - but it’s important that you keep up to date.<\/p><p>Also make sure you give your bike a quick once over every time you ride. You need to look at:<\/p><p><\/p><p>° Tyres - check the pressure when the tyres are cold. Remember the correct PSI will be listed on a factory sticker somewhere on your bike.<\/p><p>° Wheels - if you have spoked wheels make sure you check for any missing or loose spokes before you set off. <br\/><br\/>°Brakes - <a href=\"https:\/\/youtu.be\/IbqYLB-eT3E\" title=\"https:\/\/youtu.be\/IbqYLB-eT3E\">a quick check of your motorcycle’s brake discs<\/a> is important and easy to do! You don’t have to do this every time, but every six months should do the trick.<\/p><p>Checking can take a bit of time, but it’s all worth it when you can ride away with confidence.<\/p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "bd350321-2094-4451-ae70-e762f545bdb4",
        "template--15787414028484__c49dabfc-f0bd-4632-a097-f3ec01ded10c-166999440929263ebf-0"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "desktop_content_position": "left",
        "content_alignment": "left",
        "color_scheme": "#ffffff",
        "full_width": true,
        "padding_top": 40,
        "padding_bottom": 52
      }
    },
    "3c4e33dc-98ee-4ca5-ac08-4e21a2091339": {
      "type": "loop-article-richtext",
      "blocks": {
        "530cf2fd-86c1-457b-9a64-ed1762d6b439": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "6. Wear Bright Coloured Clothing",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "template--15787414028484__3c4e33dc-98ee-4ca5-ac08-4e21a2091339-1669994657dc93d8d6-0": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Being seen on the roads is vital. As good as black leather looks, you need to cramp your style with a high visibility top or colorful clothing (sorry). If the idea of a vest isn’t appealing to you, there are hi-vis belts that cost next to nothing and are just as effective.<br\/><br\/>Loving the idea of making yourself as seen as possible? Go all out with retro-reflective strips to the wheel rims, fairings, tail light and panniers.<\/p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "530cf2fd-86c1-457b-9a64-ed1762d6b439",
        "template--15787414028484__3c4e33dc-98ee-4ca5-ac08-4e21a2091339-1669994657dc93d8d6-0"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "desktop_content_position": "left",
        "content_alignment": "left",
        "color_scheme": "#ffffff",
        "full_width": true,
        "padding_top": 40,
        "padding_bottom": 52
      }
    },
    "6e1b53a3-52ff-407e-b73e-447fbbec60fb": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "template--15787414028484__6e1b53a3-52ff-407e-b73e-447fbbec60fb-166999406493e260cb-0": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "7.Ride Within Your Skill Level",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "template--15787414028484__6e1b53a3-52ff-407e-b73e-447fbbec60fb-166999406493e260cb-1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>I know, I know, we sound like a buzzkill. But motorcycle riding is a skill and it takes time to learn it properly. You may be happy and comfortable to cruise around town, but you might need a bit more practice before hitting the motorway.<\/p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "template--15787414028484__6e1b53a3-52ff-407e-b73e-447fbbec60fb-166999406493e260cb-0",
        "template--15787414028484__6e1b53a3-52ff-407e-b73e-447fbbec60fb-166999406493e260cb-1"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Two_Motorcyclists_Walking_Back_To_Their_Bike.jpg",
        "image_3": "shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Two_Motorcyclists_Walking_Back_To_Their_Bike.jpg",
        "height": "adapt",
        "desktop_image_width": "medium",
        "image_property": "cover",
        "layout": "image_first",
        "desktop_content_position": "top",
        "desktop_content_alignment": "left",
        "content_layout": "no-overlap",
        "color_scheme": "background-1",
        "mobile_content_alignment": "left",
        "padding_top": 36,
        "padding_bottom": 36
      }
    },
    "bad88747-7ffc-493c-bd9a-52bd5480e61c": {
      "type": "loop-article-richtext",
      "blocks": {
        "template--15787414028484__bad88747-7ffc-493c-bd9a-52bd5480e61c-1669995511320ae8d4-0": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Saying that, it’s important to challenge yourself in order to grow your skills and experience more. Just take it at your own pace and use your own judgment - don’t try to keep up with people who have been riding for a lot longer.<\/p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "template--15787414028484__bad88747-7ffc-493c-bd9a-52bd5480e61c-1669995511320ae8d4-0"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "desktop_content_position": "left",
        "content_alignment": "left",
        "color_scheme": "#ffffff",
        "full_width": true,
        "padding_top": 40,
        "padding_bottom": 52
      }
    },
    "8c390d66-65af-4096-8ff2-07096a96f058": {
      "type": "loop-article-richtext",
      "blocks": {
        "224ed04a-fa84-4cb3-87ea-95f441b00c49": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "8.Make Sure Your Passengers Are Safe",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "template--15787414028484__8c390d66-65af-4096-8ff2-07096a96f058-1669995586c9633c69-0": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Carrying a passenger is a big part of the fun. Shared trips and experiences - it’s the ultimate road trip!<br\/><br\/>But with passengers, a little education goes a long way:<\/p><p><\/p><p>° Make sure they have the right gear (the same as you)<br\/><br\/>° Ask them not to distract you while you’re driving, focus is everything<br\/><br\/>° Explain what turning can feel like so they don’t panic<br\/><br\/>Some passengers may know what to expect, but many won’t. And if it’s your first time taking a passenger, have a practice first in a safe space like a car park. Then you can hit the road.<\/p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "224ed04a-fa84-4cb3-87ea-95f441b00c49",
        "template--15787414028484__8c390d66-65af-4096-8ff2-07096a96f058-1669995586c9633c69-0"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "desktop_content_position": "left",
        "content_alignment": "left",
        "color_scheme": "#ffffff",
        "full_width": true,
        "padding_top": 40,
        "padding_bottom": 52
      }
    },
    "89a9a94f-b138-4ac2-ad6d-4ad9d108a101": {
      "type": "loop-article-richtext",
      "blocks": {
        "cf099ea0-d08f-46d5-a6a2-56ac2ab64089": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Final Thoughts",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "template--15787414028484__89a9a94f-b138-4ac2-ad6d-4ad9d108a101-1669995586c9633c69-0": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Motorcycles are there to be enjoyed. But they can be dangerous, too. Remember to be aware of other drivers - you have no control over their actions, but you can anticipate their movements and adjust yours accordingly.<br\/><br\/>And a final reminder to<a href=\"https:\/\/www.loopearplugs.com\/pages\/earplugs-for-motorcycle\" title=\"https:\/\/www.loopearplugs.com\/pages\/earplugs-for-motorcycle\"> protect your ears<\/a>. They deserve it.<\/p>"
          }
        }
      },
